This is the Perl distribution File-Find-Upwards.

INSTALLATION

File-Find-Upwards installation is straightforward. If your CPAN shell is
set up, you should just be able to do

    % cpan File::Find::Upwards

Download it, unpack it, then build it as per the usual:

    % perl Makefile.PL
    % make && make test

Then install it:

    % make install

DOCUMENTATION

File-Find-Upwards documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    % perldoc File::Find::Upwards

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

